cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the abuse of online social networks for spam and fraud, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves data analysis and clustering to identify campaigns, which could be classified under information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SOC). The use of multiple platforms and the detection of spam accounts could also be related to social informatics (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of phone numbers in spam campaigns, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) as it involves the use of telephony channels.
